# Claude memory template

Seed for Claude Code's **per-project persistent memory** — a plain-markdown
graph (atomic `nodes/` linked via `[[wikilinks]]`), a session `journal/`, and a
mutable `state.md` the daily standup reads. No services, no dependencies; you
can open, edit, or delete any file in any editor and Claude picks it up next
session.

This replaces the old prose `CLAUDE_MEMORY_SETUP.md` guide: instead of a
document describing how to build the system, this **is** the system, ready to
copy into place.

## Where memory lives

Claude Code loads memory from a path derived from the project's absolute path,
with `/` replaced by `-`:

```
$HOME/.claude/projects/<project-slug>/memory/
# e.g. $HOME/{{ project_name }}
#   ->  $HOME/.claude/projects/-home-mark-projects-{{ project_name }}/memory/
```

`MEMORY.md` at that path is auto-loaded into context at every session start.

## Install

> The Kaertech project's live memory already exists at its slug path. Use this
> only to **re-seed** (after wiping), to bootstrap a **fresh machine**, or to
> seed **another project**. The installer refuses to overwrite existing memory.

From the project you want memory for:

```bash
bash .claude/memory-template/scripts/init-memory.sh
# or target a specific project dir:
bash .claude/memory-template/scripts/init-memory.sh /home/mark/projects/some-odoo
```

It computes the slug, copies this template to the slug path, substitutes the
`__MEMORY_DIR__` placeholder with the real absolute path, drops the installer +
this README from the live copy, and makes the scripts executable.

**Manual alternative:** copy everything except `README.md` and
`scripts/init-memory.sh` to the slug path, then replace every `__MEMORY_DIR__`
occurrence with that absolute path (`grep -rl __MEMORY_DIR__`).

## What's inside

- `MEMORY.md` — always-loaded index + the standup procedure (Claude runs it first thing).
- `state.md` / `state_counter` — current open items + monotonic ID source.
- `nodes/`
  - `conventions_*` — how to write nodes, journals, tags; the full behavior protocol.
  - `bootstrap_questions.md` — onboarding questions to seed `user_role` and project facts.
  - `user_role.md` — **stub**; fill it in on first bootstrap.
  - `reference_*` — 8 general Odoo framework facts (search kwarg, ir.cron trigger,
    m2m domain/picker, mute_logger, savepoint, autovacuum, o2m active_test) as
    starter knowledge. Verified on Odoo 17; the mechanisms hold on 16.
- `journal/` — chronological session logs (one file per day).
- `scripts/`
  - `standup.sh` — daily continuity render (idempotent; GNU + BSD/macOS `date`/`stat`).
  - `digest.sh` — list unprocessed `raw/` drops.
  - `raw-drop.sh` — quick capture into `raw/` from a shell alias.
  - `init-memory.sh` — this installer (not copied into live memory).

Node taxonomy: `user` (who they are), `feedback` (rules the user gave Claude —
always with **Why** + **How to apply**), `project` (non-obvious project facts),
`reference` (framework/external facts). See `nodes/conventions_node_format.md`.

## Optional: raw-drop alias

```bash
alias raw='bash $HOME/.claude/projects/<project-slug>/memory/scripts/raw-drop.sh'
```

Then `raw https://…` or `raw "idea: …"` captures into `raw/` for a later `digest.sh` pass.
